dct_description_sm: Alternate title: Hokko. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:6,000. Polyconic projection. Compiled from aerial photgraphy dated October 1944 by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa; 25,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2117-I SW, 1944. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System.With a glossary. Name has been changed to Pei-kang. Relief shown by spot heights. Military grid. With a glossary. Classified roads and trails, railroads, and areas of vegetation and cultivation are shown. Marginal maps and diagrams: Index to boundaries -- Coverage diagram. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. East Decimal Degree 120.300000. West Decimal Degree 120.283333. South Decimal Degree 23.583333. North Decimal Degree 23.566667.
